Thie CC list on these messages is getting long....

I support Christian's comments.
I suggest that the RARE WG1 consider the proposal at the next meeting,
and that we take the following action:
- We recommend the DNS strategy as an interim strategy until X.500 becomes
  available
- We delegate authority to one of our members to start up the service
  as soon as possible.

We will NEED:
- A new version of the memo, with all the "maybe"s replaced by "is".
  It would be nice for it to have official RFC status.
- An organization that is willing to run the initial name server and
  to make the tables on a regular basis.
The RARE MHS Project Team is a natural candidate to make the tables, and
I am investigating whether or not UNINETT can make the resources that
are required for the name server available.

                       Harald Tveit Alvestrand
                       RARE MHS project leader

